                      <span>2003-05-17</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This book is one of my favorite non-fiction books.  The beauty of this book is that the main points are in Ghandi's exact quotes while the flow of the arguments are edited by his biographer, Louis Fischer, to give a great feel of direction.  Because Ghandi edited his own newspaper his life-changing views are abundant and easily accessible.  If only this book were read by all leaders of people.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Best Gandhi book available.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
